{"id":"project-LICHEN-qnw4","title":"context.rs: Mo::MatchMapping always returns false (unimplemented)","description":"File: rust/lichen-schc/src/context.rs
Lines: 74-77

Category: CORRECTNESS / API MISUSE

The rule_matches() function has a stub implementation for Mo::MatchMapping that always returns false:
```rust
Mo::MatchMapping => {
    // Mapping table not yet implemented in rules.rs
    // For now, return false (no mapping = no match)
    return false;
}
```

RFC 8724 section 7.4 defines match-mapping as matching against an ordered list of values. The current implementation makes it impossible for any rule using MatchMapping to ever match.

Impact: Any rule configured with Mo::MatchMapping will never be selected, forcing traffic to fall back to less efficient rules or uncompressed mode.

Fix: Either implement the mapping table lookup, or mark Mo::MatchMapping as unimplemented at compile time (e.g., remove it from the enum and document the limitation).","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:40:55.904339Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:40:55.904372Z"}

